# Routing

## URL map (v1)

| Path | Access | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| `/` | public | Home / landing |
| `/docs` | public | Documentation index (redirects to first category) |
| `/docs/category/[slug]` | public | Category section index listing child docs |
| `/docs/[slug]` | public | Single published doc |
| `/login` | public | User sign-in |
| `/admin/login` | public | Admin sign-in; one-time create-admin when bootstrapping |
| `/invite/[token]` | public | Accept admin invitation |
| `/login/two-factor` | admin | TOTP challenge after admin sign-in |
| `/admin` | admin | Dashboard |
| `/admin/documents` | admin | Document list |
| `/admin/documents/new` | admin | Create document |
| `/admin/documents/[id]` | admin | CodeMirror editor |
| `/admin/users` | admin | Invite and manage admins |
| `/admin/settings` | admin | Site + account settings |
| `/admin/security/2fa` | admin | Mandatory 2FA enrollment |
| `/api/auth/*` | public | Better Auth API (hooks + catch-all route) |
| `/api/document-media/[slug]` | public | Same-origin PDF proxy for in-page embeds |

## Groups

- **Public:** `/`, `/docs`, `/docs/*`, `/login`, `/admin/login`, `/invite/*`
- **Protected:** `/admin`, `/admin/*` (except `/admin/login`) — require admin role via `requireAdmin()`
- **Auth:** `/login` redirects signed-in users to `/`; `/admin/login` redirects admins to `/admin`

## Conventions

- Use `resolve()` from `$app/paths` for internal links
- `/admin/**` uses `+layout.server.ts` for auth guard (`/admin/login` is exempt)
- Unpublished docs return 404 for public; admin can preview when logged in
